    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-06-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-06-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="352"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d352">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.796/141½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Assistant Secretary of State</hi>
                        (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Acheson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-23">June 23,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Acheson</hi>: The Argentine Ambassador left with me
                    this morning a copy of an <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> which he left with
                    the Department on May 21 last.<note n="29" xml:id="d352fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> The Argentine Navy is very anxious to
                    have us grant the request comprised in this memorandum. It is disturbed that we
                    have not yet given any indication of a favorable attitude.</p>
                <p>I shall appreciate it if you will have some one in your office follow this
                    through and see what the situation may be.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>S[<hi rend="smallcaps">umner</hi>] W[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >elles</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
